				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Construction waste refers to materials generated during the construction, renovation, or demolition of buildings and civil-engineering structures. It includes a variety of materials such as steel, wood products, drywall, plaster, brick, clay tile, asphalt shingles, concrete, and asphalt concrete. Construction waste management is the process of planning, tracking, and reducing the waste produced on construction sites, with the aim of minimizing the impact on landfills and promoting the reuse and recycling of materials.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">建筑垃圾是指在建筑和土木工程结构的建造、翻新或拆除过程中产生的材料。它包括各种材料，如钢材、木制品、干墙、石膏、砖、粘土砖、沥青瓦、混凝土和沥青混凝土。建筑废物管理是对建筑工地产生的废物进行规划、跟踪和减少的过程，目的是最大限度地减少对垃圾填埋场的影响，促进材料的再利用和再循环。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
